        <updateDate>2018-10-24T14:35:13Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Ensuring Diverse Leadership Act of</b> <b>2018</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Federal Reserve Act to require that in making the appointment of a president, a Federal Reserve Bank must interview at least one individual reflective of gender diversity and one reflective of racial or ethnic diversity.</p> <p>The bill amends numerous banking-, finance-, and trade-related Acts to make references to officials (including those to the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System) gender-neutral. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
